text: Washington Heights is one of the 77 official community areas of Chicago, Illinois. It is located on the far south side of the city. It has a population of 27,453. The CTA red line stop at 95th St. is also available along the Dan Ryan Expressway in nearby Roseland. Washington Heights is a stronghold of the Democratic Party. In the 2016 presidential election, Washington Heights cast 13,709 votes for Hillary Clinton and cast 229 votes for Donald Trump. ==References== Category:Community areas of Chicago
